From: Andriy Gapon <avg@FreeBSD.org>
Date: Mon, 17 Feb 2025 11:27:40 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Stop forcing C++11 with newer Boost

The root cause of build failures was forcing -std=c++11 while newer
Boost.Math requires at least C++14.

---
 CMakeLists.txt | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index c37e0810..471ed1f0 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -442,7 +441,6 @@ add_definitions(-DQT_NO_KEYWORDS)
 add_definitions(-D__STDC_LIMIT_MACROS)
 add_definitions(-Wall -Wextra)
-add_definitions(-std=c++11)
 add_definitions(-DBOOST_MATH_DISABLE_FLOAT128=1)
 
 if(ENABLE_FLOW)
